<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-003-189 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 574 548</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 3 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Encore Computer's new software pricing strategy.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Encore Computer Corp. (Prices and rates).andO;Product:   Encore Computer Encore 90 (Minicomputer) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     LicensingSoftware PackagesPrice.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Encore Computer's New Software Pricing Strategy 12/03/01 FORT LAUDERDALE,FLORIDA, U.S.A., 1991 DEC 3 (NB) -- Encore Computer Corporation has announceda new software pricing strategy for its mainframe software products that runon its Encore 90 family of computers.andM;Under the new program, called concurrent-use licensing, users pay for aspecific number of simultaneous accesses to a product, rather than thetraditional licensing method of unlimited user access to a system.andM;&quot;This buy only what you need concept is an equitable way of charging forsoftware,&quot; said Mary Bilancia, manager of product marketing for large systemsat Encore.andP;  Bilancia said that in the past, customers were required to payfor unlimited software usage upfront, with the charge varying for differentsystem classifications.andP;  Under that system, some customers were penalized forlow volume software usage in large system configurations.andP;  Under the newpricing strategy, users purchase what they need upfront and pay the sameamount per user, regardless of system size.andP;  Because pricing is based or aper-seat or per-user basis, some.andP;  Customers may be required to purchase aminimum number of concurrent-use licenses.andM;Encore said that concurrent-use licensing applies to a select group of Encore90 family products.andP;  For layered products, licensing is based on concurrentuser access to a particular product.andP;  For real-time kernels, licensing isbased on concurrent use of processor resources within the system.andM;Encore designs, manufactures, distributes, and support mainframe systems forreal-time and on-line processing applications.andM;(Jim Mallory/19911202/Press contact: Kerry Foley, Encore, 305-797-5443)</TEXT></DOC>